14:
But I and my people are not really able to give anything to you,\q2 because everything that we have comes from you;
\q2 the things that we have given to you are only the things that we have received from you.
\q1

15:
You know that we are like foreigners and strangers to you, as our ancestors were.\q2 Our years here on earth are like a shadow that disappears quickly;
\q2 we know that there is nothing that can enable us to escape dying.


\q1
